2.

DSSS is Direct Sequence Spread Spectrum.It works by spreading signal across bandwidth using chipsets.A bit is encoded as multiple bits.
It is nise resistant and used in 802.11b

FHSS stands for Frequency Hopping Spread Spectrum.It works by jumping across different frequencies and avoids interference. It was used in early Wifi.

