6.
Guard Interval refers to time gap between 2 OFDM symbols to prevent Inter Symbol Interference(ISI)

Two types:
1.Short Guard : Provides more speed(more symbol/sec and high throughput) but risky in noisy environment.(Eg. 0.4 microsec in 802.11n)
2.Long Guard  : Provides high reliability but is comparatively slow.(Eg. 0.8 microsec in 802.11n)

