10.
PPDU (Physical Protocol Data Unit):
PPDU is the complete PHY-layer frame that goes over the air that is what is transmitted at the phy layer.
It contains:
[Preamble][PHY Header][PSDU]


PLCP (Physical Layer Convergence Protocol)
PLCP is the interface between MAC and Physical layer.
It takes MAC data (PSDU) and formats/frames it for transmission.
PLCP:
1. Encapsulation
PSDU is wrapped into PPDU
2.PLCP adds:
Preamble + PHY Header
3. Makes receiver understand transmission
The PHY header tells:
modulation (QAM level)
coding rate
number of spatial streams
packet length

Without PLCP:
Receiver cannot decode signal

PMD (Physical Medium Dependent)
PMD is the lowest part of PHY layer that actually transmits signals.
PMD:
1. Modulation
Converts bits into signals using:
PSK
QAM
OFDM/OFDMA
2. Applies RF processing
upconversion to RF frequency
amplification
antenna transmission
3. Uses MIMO
multiple antennas
spatial streams
4. Transmits over air

Final output:

010101 → electromagnetic waves → air

